                "accordion_row_7NKhzc": {
                  "type": "_accordion-row",
                  "settings": {
                    "heading": "¿Cuál es la mejor forma de enlazar mis DM?",
                    "open_by_default": false,
                    "icon": "none",
                    "width": 20
                  },
                  "blocks": {
                    "text_xDMEKD": {
                      "type": "text",
                      "settings": {
                        "text": "<p>However you’d like to show off your style or is most comfortable! With a new pair, it may feel good to leave one or two sets of eyelets left open at the top. This keeps the top part of the shoe from feeling abrasive while also being laced high enough that you feel secure when you walk while they’re shaping to you. Some people like the look and feel of wrapping the laces around the ankle. If you’re still unsure, we put together a guide of our favorite<a href=\"https://www.drmartens.com/us/en/guides/how-to-lace-boots-shoes\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Ways to lace DM’s</span></a>.<a href=\"https://www.drmartens.com/us/en/c/07597600\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Shop our range of laces</span></a>to switch up your style and customize your look.<br/><br/><strong>Tip:</strong>We’d recommend re-lacing any new pair of shoes so that the aglet (tip of the lace) comes from the underside of the eyelet hole for a more secure fit.</p>",
                        "width": "100%",
                        "max_width": "none",
                        "alignment": "left",
                        "type_preset": "custom",
                        "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
                        "weight": "",
                        "font_size": "1rem",
